=== VERIFICATION OUTPUT ===
Testing: Hybrid Raft/Paxos flexible quorum read latency
Hypothesis: Flexible quorums (R+W>N) should yield lower read latency than strict majority.

Running with N=5 nodes, simulating 1000 read operations...
Strict majority quorum (3/5): mean latency = 12.4ms, p99 = 28.1ms
Flexible quorum (R=2, W=4): mean latency = 8.7ms, p99 = 19.3ms

However, under 1-node failure scenario:
Strict majority (3/4 available): mean latency = 14.2ms, p99 = 31.5ms, availability = 100%
Flexible quorum (R=2, W=4, only 4 available): WRITE UNAVAILABLE — cannot form write quorum

result = {"verified": false, "reason": "Flexible quorums reduce read latency under normal conditions but sacrifice write availability under failure — the claim omits this critical trade-off"}